        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You grew up in the pressure cooker of boarding school. While most of your classmates were wealthy and privileged, your parents both worked overtime to pay for your tuition. So you learned quickly how to make yourself useful, to your fellow students and teachers alike. Whether it was helping someone with their homework or helping clean a classroom after hours, you were always able to do it. Doubtless this flexibility is what attracted your sire to you, a Nosferatu of the Camarilla. But something happened, something went wrong. Your sire called you Caitiff, because neither did your appearance change at all after your Embrace, you also did not manifest any of the traditional powers of the Nosferatu. Your sire rejected you, and you, already disoriented and hungry with the recent change you'd been through, fought back. You ended up committing diablerie against him, and you've never felt so good or so alive as you did while doing it. A few years later, you caught a Brujah Anarch unawares and repeated the act - though this time, it was not without cost, and you realized that the Brujah's rage had become your rage. You struck out on your own after that, dodging Hunters and scourges alike until you found the Sabbat. They took you in, taught you and gave you a purpose. You use your inherent flexiblity to be whatever is needed, whether that's someone who can use mortals, someone who can stand up in a fight or anything in between."
        ],
